oai_dc:dc.dc:title: EXPERIMENTAL STUDY OF THE HYDRAULIC BEHAVIOUR OF INCLINED GROYNE SYSTEMS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Barcelo, Julio Patriarca
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: hydraulic behavior
inclined groin system
groin
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This paper presents the results of an experimental study on the behaviour of inclined groynes and a short discussion on the optimization of groyne systems It supplements a paper presented at the XI Coastal Engineering Conference (London, 1968) In the present paper both studies are applied to the design of a groyne system looated to the south of the Tagus estuary (near Lisbon)j where a serious erosion has been under way.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 12 (1970): Proceedings of 12th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Washington, D.C., 1970.; 65
